Grammy award-winning singer Wizkid has officially equalled a 27-year- record on the Billboard charts with his classic hit album “Made in Lagos.” Besides being the highest and the longest-charting Nigerian artist on the Billboard World Album charts, Big Wiz game stands elevated as he has now joined other African legends to have the longest-charting album on the Billboard charts. The 31-year-old “Ojuelegba” singer has a tie with Cesaria Evora to have the longest-charting album on the Billboard World Album Charts with 66 weeks.   Sugar daddies don’t bankroll me, says…     Most wealthy Nigerians into rituals, Seun Kuti alleges     I’m not in a haste to win Grammy- Bella Shmurda   The Cape Verdean singer, Cesaria Evora, with her Grammy award-winning album, ‘Cesária’, had spent a total of 66 weeks while clinching the number 2 position, thereby making her the only African to spend that long on the charts. - Advertisement - Wizkid has equalled Cesaria Evora’s record with his “Made in Lagos” album while showing the likelihood of overshooting same. Thus, in a week time, Starboy will totally shatter the record to become the highest-charting African on the Billboard World album charts. SPONSORED